The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Extra cover at Eden today
                                                                                                                       7                                      Extra cover at Eden today
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Following Saturdays blast at the Chinnaswamy Stadium in Bangalore, a tight security blanket has been thrown around Eden Gardens, where the Kolkata Knight Riders play the Mumbai Indians in the Indian Premier League on Monday.         
	A contingent comprising 2000 policemen, along with sniffer dogs and plainclothes cops, will be deployed to sterilise the stadium and its vicinity. We have decided to engage 500 additional policemen on Monday. In the previous matches, we deployed 1500 policemen, said Jawed Shamim, joint commissioner of police, headquarters.         
	Shamim said two arterial thoroughfares  Auckland Road and Kings Way  would be sealed from 4pm as part of the security measures. Police further said that spectators will not be allowed in with bags.                                                                                                                     
